<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,796,1254]" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[199,305,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
This rare species, previously known from the 
<typeStatus box="[826,924,976,1002]" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
only, was fully described and is easily recognized by color and distribution. Although we were unable to study the 
<typeStatus box="[941,1042,1012,1038]" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
, the second and third known specimens are reliably consistent with the description and photographs provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P." box="[1048,1308,1048,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref9666" refString="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2007) Tropical and subtropical velvet ants of the genus Dasymutilla Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) with descriptions of 45 new species. Zootaxa 1487, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="2007">Manley &amp; Pitts (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P." pageId="12" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref9666" refString="Manley, D. G. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2007) Tropical and subtropical velvet ants of the genus Dasymutilla Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) with descriptions of 45 new species. Zootaxa 1487, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="2007">Manley &amp; Pitts (2007)</bibRefCitation>
made no remarks regarding 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Manley &amp; Pitts" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[600,807,1084,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellatrix">
<emphasis box="[600,807,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Quwitilla bellatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(then 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manley &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2007" box="[877,1115,1084,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dasymutilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellatrix">
<emphasis box="[877,1115,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Dasymutilla bellatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) except that it was similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[151,318,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blattoserica">
<emphasis box="[151,318,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Q. blattoserica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(then 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[388,555,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blattoserica">
<emphasis box="[388,555,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">D. blattoserica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Manley &amp; Pitts" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[577,784,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellatrix">
<emphasis box="[577,784,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Quwitilla bellatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indeed morphologically closer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1187,1354,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blattoserica">
<emphasis box="[1187,1354,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Q. blattoserica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartholomay &amp; Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Suarez" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[151,300,1156,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Quwitilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[151,300,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="273">Q. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and might in fact be a color variant, and therefore a synonym, of the latter. We refrain from calling it so for the moment based on the limited material available from diurnal species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1053,1170,1192,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
west of the Andes, their apparently disparate ranges, and the fact that we have yet to see an intermediate color form between these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
